    <wa-tab-panel name="running">

        <h2 class="wa-visually-hidden">Running</h2>
        <section>
            <h3>My Running History</h3>

            <h4>2020 and before</h4>
            <p>Most of the time, my rowing training has included some running since the beginning but it was sporadic 
                and I ended up only running once or twice every couple of weeks. I was decent at running where I was 
                faster than most or all of the other rowers but was not very fast at running itself. In 2020, I had 
                the goal of breaking 20min for 5k but despite running 20:0X a couple of times, I never broke 20min 
                that year and had a rough New Years Eve 5k race to finish the year far from my goal.</p>
            
            <h4>2021 and after</h4>
            <div class="wa-flank:end wa-align-items-start" style="--content-percentage: 55%;">
            <p>In 2021, I decided I would get better at running. I decided I would consistently run a bit after one 
                of my daily ergs. I seemed to be getting a bit better and in late January did a 5k Time Trial as part 
                of a virtual 5k race. I ended up going sub 19min despite struggling to get close to even 20min a couple 
                weeks before. Since then, my running has gotten significantly better, especially for the Half Marathon 
                distance. After going 18:01 off GPS in May of 2021, my 5k stagnated till I finally broke 18min at a 5k 
                race on New Years Eve in 2022. My Half Marathon has been consistently dropping over time, since breaking 
                90min in March of 2021 it has dropped over 10min. 
                After my rowing career finished I ran my first marathon that summer and qualified for the Boston Marathon 
                which <a href="https://www.strava.com/activities/14247989770">I raced</a> the following spring.
                I am currently focused on triathlon but may switch to a marathon focus in the future.</p>
            <img src="/photos/BostonMarathon2025.jpg" alt="Richard Sollee in the last mile of the Boston Marathon 2025" style="width: 50ch;"/>
            </div>
        </section>

